<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>hooveri</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>thyrsiflorus</i> and <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>tomentosum</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>coulteri</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>lambertiana</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>ponderosa</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>chrysolepis</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 8 m; canopy continuous. Herbaceous layer sparse. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Arctostaphylos hooveri</i> > 60% relative cover (Borchert et al. 2004).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Broad ridges, steep ridgetops, south-facing slopes. Soils are shallow to moderately deep coarse sands and sandy clay loams.  </div>
</div>

        
